      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty strong take. But what about the downsides? Like, isn't nationalism often the root cause of major conflicts, xenophobia, and even wars? It seems like it can be really exclusionary. Wouldn't you say it's more of a risk than a benefit in a globalized world?",
